cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.DM, cs.SY

This paper is about a variant of Genetic Programming (GP) called Geometric Semantic Genetic Programming (GSGP) that is used for supervised machine learning problems, particularly in the task of symbolic regression. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses the issue of exponential growth of individuals generated by the geometric semantic crossover operator, which is a common problem in evolutionary algorithms. This suggests that the paper could also belong to categories related to optimization and search algorithms, such as cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Additionally, the paper proposes a new method for individual simplification, which involves aggregating repeated structures and coefficients. This suggests that the paper could also belong to categories related to data structures and algorithms, such as cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) and cs.SY (Systems and Control).
